#: ../../source/api/element.rst:2 18f5e2afa43e49acb049fb52f05ebd6b
msgid "tensormesh.element"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:6 1aba8b22ac394a08a6278abc35479c77
msgid ""
"The :mod:`tensormesh.element` module is organised in three tiers, each "
"aimed at a different audience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:9 f09718e1f84a494fa6280a1d5794bb35
msgid ""
":ref:`api-element-transformation` — the only thing most users call "
"directly. If you are writing a new assembler or computing shape values / "
"gradients / ``J×W`` at quadrature points, this is your interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:13 ae09fd50150b4ab8a658c56e69515900
msgid ""
":ref:`api-element-catalog` — the seven reference shapes and the "
"string-↔-class registry. Read this when you need to know *which* type "
"string corresponds to which class, what its facet shape is, or how its "
"node ordering compares to Gmsh / VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:17 69cb683753b74600be96b0fcb5b7b5ae
msgid ""
":ref:`api-element-internals` — basis builders, quadrature factories, "
"facet-normal helpers, and the :class:`~tensormesh.element.Polynomial` "
"machinery. Read this only if you are adding a new element type or "
"quadrature rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:26 c7df69b2286a41228f48ca75a52dbb8e
msgid "Transformation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/element.rst:28 8119db9549f148979c75f4d9076d099c
msgid ""
"The workhorse: given a mesh's points + connectivity + element type, a "
":class:`~tensormesh.Transformation` caches the per-element Jacobian, "
"shape-function values, shape-function gradients, quadrature "
"points/weights, and their facet analogues. Every built-in assembler in "
":mod:`tensormesh.assemble` ultimately reads from a ``Transformation``; "
"custom assemblers should too."
msgstr ""

#: 53a680893d9842dca775fa6255116ec4 of
#: tensormesh.element.transformation.Transformation:1
msgid "Reference-to-physical mapping for one element-type block of a mesh."
msgstr ""

#: 3dac75a4785d436588ade0ce54695cde of
#: tensormesh.element.transformation.Transformation:3
msgid ""
"Holds the per-element Jacobian, shape-function values, shape-function "
"gradients, quadrature points/weights, and their facet analogues — all the"
" geometric ingredients an assembler needs to integrate a weak form. "
"Subclass of :class:`torch.nn.Module`, so every cached tensor is a buffer "
"and follows the module's ``.to()``/``.cuda()``/``.double()``."
msgstr ""

