#: ../../source/api/element.rst:141 78e038da140e43f4813044d8d0d0eabe
msgid ""
"**Polynomial space.** :class:`tensormesh.element.Polynomial` represents a"
" single multivariate polynomial; :class:`tensormesh.element.Polynomials` "
"represents an arbitrarily-shaped batch. They are the building blocks of "
"every shape-function set: :meth:`~tensormesh.Element.get_basis_fns` "
"solves a small Vandermonde system to obtain the Lagrange-interpolation "
"coefficients on top of a chosen polynomial space (full ``poly_exp``, "
"tensor-product ``tens_exp``, or the pyramid / prism ad-hoc spaces). To "
"add a new element you typically override "
":meth:`~tensormesh.Element.get_polynomial` to return the right polynomial"
" space and let the base class produce the basis functions for you."
msgstr ""

